{"type":"route","meta":{"status":200,"headers":{"content-type":"text/plain;charset=UTF-8","x-next-cache-tags":"_N_T_/layout,_N_T_/llms-full.txt/layout,_N_T_/llms-full.txt/route,_N_T_/llms-full.txt"}},"body":"# Calendar & Bookings (/docs/calendar)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Calendar is where all your appointments live. It shows your team's full schedule side by side — one column per staff member — so you can see everyone's day at a glance and book new appointments in seconds.\n\n***\n\nHow the Calendar is laid out [#how-the-calendar-is-laid-out]\n\nWhen you open the Calendar you'll see:\n\n* **A column for each staff member** — each person has their own lane with their profile photo and name at the top\n* **Time slots running down the page** — the interval (15, 30, or 45 min) is set in [Settings → Calendar](/docs/settings#calendar)\n* **A red line showing the current time** — so you always know where you are in the day\n* **Appointment cards** — each card shows the client name, service, and time range\n* **Navigation bar at the top** — use **Today*&#x2A;, &#x2A;*\\<*&#x2A;, and &#x2A;*>** to move between days, or click the date to jump to a specific day\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n  The **+ Add** button in the top right corner is for selling products, memberships, or vouchers directly — it opens a cart where you select the items and a client. It is **not** for creating appointments. To book an appointment, click directly on an empty time slot in a staff column.\n</Callout>\n\n<img alt=\"Quick Sale Cart\" src=\"__img0\" />\n\n***\n\nBooking a new appointment [#booking-a-new-appointment]\n\nTo create an appointment, click on any **empty time slot** in a staff member's column. A booking panel will slide open on the right side of the screen.\n\n<img alt=\"Booking an Appointment\" src=\"__img1\" />\n\nStep 1 — Select a client [#step-1--select-a-client]\n\nThe left side of the panel shows your client list. You can:\n\n* **Search** by name or phone number\n* Select an **existing client** from the list\n* Choose **Walk-In Customer** if the client isn't registered\n* Click **Add new client** to create a new profile on the spot\n\n<Callout type=\"tip\">\n  You don't need to pre-register a client. Walk-In Customer works perfectly for first-time or unregistered visitors.\n</Callout>\n\nOnce you select a client, their name, phone, and email will be confirmed on screen. You can click **Change Client** if you need to swap to someone else, or **View \\[Client]'s Profile** to open their full history.\n\nStep 2 — Add services [#step-2--add-services]\n\nOn the right side of the panel, click **+ Add service**. A service picker will open showing all your available services with their price and duration.\n\n* Tick the **checkbox** next to any service you want to add\n* You can select multiple services at once\n* Click **Done** when you're finished\n\nThe selected services appear in the **Appointment** panel showing the time, duration, assigned team, and price. The total updates automatically at the bottom.\n\nStep 3 — Save [#step-3--save]\n\nClick **Save*&#x2A;. The appointment is created instantly and appears as a card on the calendar. A green &#x2A;*\"Appointment created successfully\"** notification will confirm it.\n\n***\n\nAppointment card hover [#appointment-card-hover]\n\nHover over any appointment card on the calendar to see a quick summary popup showing:\n\n* The time range (e.g., 14:30 – 15:30)\n* The current status badge (e.g., **Scheduled**)\n* The client's name and phone number\n* The service name, team, duration, and price\n\n***\n\nEditing an appointment [#editing-an-appointment]\n\nClick on an existing appointment card to open the **Edit Appointment** panel. It works the same as the booking panel — you can change the client, add or remove services, or update the time or Status.\n\n<img alt=\"Managing Appointment Status\" src=\"__img2\" />\n\nAt the top of the edit panel you'll see status action buttons:\n\n| Button      | What it does                               |\n| ----------- | ------------------------------------------ |\n| **Arrived** | Marks the client as checked in and present |\n| **Start**   | Marks the service as actively in progress  |\n| **No Show** | Records that the client didn't show up     |\n| **Cancel**  | Cancels the appointment                    |\n\nThe status is reflected both on the appointment card and in the hover popup.\n\nAt the bottom of the panel you'll see two buttons:\n\n* **Save** — saves any changes you made\n* **Checkout** — moves the appointment to the payment screen to collect payment\n\n***\n\nAppointment statuses [#appointment-statuses]\n\n| Status    | What it means                          |\n| --------- | -------------------------------------- |\n| Scheduled | The appointment is booked and upcoming |\n| Arrived   | The client has arrived at the salon    |\n| Start     | The service is currently in progress   |\n| No Show   | The client didn't show up              |\n| Cancelled | The appointment was cancelled          |\n\n***\n\nBlocking time off [#blocking-time-off]\n\nNeed to mark a staff member as unavailable for a break, training, or any other reason? You can block out time without creating a real appointment.\n\n<Steps>\n  <Step>\n    Click on an empty time slot in a staff member's column and select **Block Time**.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Set the start time, end time, and an optional note so the team knows why the slot is blocked.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Click **Save**. The blocked slot will appear as a distinct card on the calendar.\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\n***\n\nGoing to checkout from the calendar [#going-to-checkout-from-the-calendar]\n\nOnce a client's appointment is done, you can take payment directly from the calendar.\n\n<Steps>\n  <Step>\n    Click on the appointment card to open the Edit Appointment panel.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Click **Checkout** at the bottom of the panel.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    The payment screen opens with the services already loaded. Follow the [Checkout](/docs/checkout) steps to apply discounts, add a tip, and collect payment.\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\n***\n\nQuick reference [#quick-reference]\n\n| Feature              | How it works                                                   |\n| -------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Staff columns        | One column per team member with their photo                    |\n| Date navigation      | Use Today, \\<, and > buttons to change the day                 |\n| Walk-in booking      | Select \"Walk-In Customer\" — no profile needed                  |\n| Multiple services    | Tick as many services as needed in the service picker          |\n| Appointment statuses | Arrived, Start, No Show, Cancel — updated from the edit panel  |\n| Hover card           | Hover an appointment to see a quick summary without opening it |\n\n\n# Catalog & Inventory (/docs/catalog)\n\n\n\nThe Catalog is where you define everything your salon offers — the services your team performs, the products you sell, membership packages, gift vouchers, and your product inventory. Think of it as the foundation that powers your bookings and checkout.\n\nClick **Catalog** in the left menu to get started. You'll see five tabs at the top: **Services**, **Products**, **Memberships**, **Vouchers**, and **Stock Audit**.\n\n***\n\nServices [#services]\n\nServices are the treatments your team performs — haircuts, color, manicures, massages, and so on. Every service you add here will be available to select when booking an appointment.\n\nAdding a service [#adding-a-service]\n\n<Steps>\n  <Step>\n    Go to **Catalog → Services** and click **Add Service**.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Give the service a **name**, choose a **category** (e.g., Hair, Nails), set the **duration** in minutes, and enter the **price**.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Make sure the status is set to **Active** — only active services show up when booking.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Click **Save**.\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\nEditing or removing a service [#editing-or-removing-a-service]\n\nClick the **Edit** icon on any service to update its details. If you want to stop a service from showing up in bookings without deleting it permanently, just toggle the status to inactive. To remove it entirely, use the **Delete** option.\n\n***\n\nProducts [#products]\n\nProducts are the retail or consumable items you sell or use in your salon — shampoos, styling products, skincare, and so on. NxCut tracks your stock levels automatically as products are sold.\n\nAdding a product [#adding-a-product]\n\n<Steps>\n  <Step>\n    Go to **Catalog → Products** and click **Add Product**.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Enter the product's **name**, **brand**, **category**, and **supplier**.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Set the **price** and enter your current **stock quantity**.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Toggle it to **Active** so it's available to add during checkout.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Click **Save**.\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\nEvery time a product is sold at checkout, your stock count goes down automatically. Use the [Stock Audit](#stock-audit) tab when you want to check your physical stock against what the system shows.\n\n***\n\nMemberships [#memberships]\n\nMemberships are prepaid session packages — a client pays upfront for a bundle of appointments (for example, 10 haircuts for the price of 8). Each time they come in and use a session, it's deducted from their balance automatically.\n\nCreating a membership [#creating-a-membership]\n\n<Steps>\n  <Step>\n    Go to **Catalog → Memberships** and click **Add Membership**.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Give the membership a **name** and choose which **service** it applies to.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Set the number of **sessions** included and the total **price**.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Optionally set an **expiry period** — for example, all sessions must be used within 12 months of purchase.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Click **Save**.\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\nOnce a client buys a membership at checkout, their session count is tracked automatically on their [client profile](/docs/clients). Sessions are used up each time they check out using that membership.\n\n***\n\nVouchers [#vouchers]\n\nVouchers are gift cards or discount codes that clients can redeem when paying for services or products. You set the value (either a fixed amount or a percentage off), and NxCut tracks how much has been used and what's left.\n\nCreating a voucher [#creating-a-voucher]\n\n<Steps>\n  <Step>\n    Go to **Catalog → Vouchers** and click **Add Voucher**.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Give the voucher a **name** and choose the discount type: a **fixed amount** (e.g., AED 100 off) or a **percentage** (e.g., 20% off).\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Create a **voucher code** — this is what the client enters at checkout.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Optionally set an **expiry date** and a **usage limit** (e.g., can only be used once).\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Click **Save**.\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n  You can check a client's remaining voucher balance and full usage history on their profile under [Clients → Voucher Activity](/docs/clients#voucher-activity).\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nStock Audit [#stock-audit]\n\nA stock audit is how you check that your physical inventory matches what NxCut thinks you have. It's good practice to run one regularly, especially if products are used during services as well as sold.\n\nA stock audit moves through three stages: **Stock Session → Stock Entry → Stock Review**. Each stage has its own status so you always know where an audit is up to.\n\n| Status      | What it means                                      |\n| ----------- | -------------------------------------------------- |\n| In Progress | The audit is open and items are being counted      |\n| Review      | Counting is done — ready to review and confirm     |\n| Completed   | The audit is finalised and can no longer be edited |\n\n***\n\nStep 1 — Stock Session [#step-1--stock-session]\n\n<Steps>\n  <Step>\n    Go to **Catalog → Stock Audit** and click **Start New Audit Session**.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Select the products you want to include in this count.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Click **Start** to begin. The audit moves to the **Stock Entry** stage.\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\n***\n\nStep 2 — Stock Entry (Counting) [#step-2--stock-entry-counting]\n\nThis is where you physically count your stock. The entry screen opens in **barcode mode** by default — just scan a product's barcode and NxCut will find it automatically and add 1 to its counted quantity. Each scan is saved instantly, so you don't need to do anything extra.\n\n<Callout type=\"tip\">\n  Scan the same product multiple times to keep adding to its count — each scan increments the quantity by 1.\n</Callout>\n\n**If you click Save Stock Audit before finishing:**\n\nA dialog will appear telling you how many products still haven't been counted (e.g., \"5 products remaining\"). The only option here is **Continue** — this sends you back to finish counting before the audit can be saved.\n\n**If you click the X (close) button before finishing:**\n\nA dialog titled &#x2A;*\"Uncounted products remaining\"** will appear, asking how you'd like to handle the items you didn't get to. You'll have two choices:\n\n* **Save uncounted as 0** — records those products as having zero stock on the shelf. Use this if you genuinely checked and found nothing.\n* **Sync counted to previous stock** — leaves those products at whatever stock value was already in the system. Use this if you simply didn't get around to counting them and don't want to affect their records.\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n  Not sure which to pick? If you didn't actually check those products, choose **Sync counted to previous stock** — that way only the items you physically counted will be updated.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nStep 3 — Stock Review [#step-3--stock-review]\n\nOnce all items are counted and saved, the audit moves to **Review** status. On this page you'll see:\n\n* An overview of every product that was counted\n* The **quantity difference** between what the system expected and what you physically counted\n* The **price difference** — the value impact of any discrepancies\n\nFrom here you can:\n\n* **Resume editing** — go back and adjust any counts before finalising\n* **Complete the audit** — confirm the counts are correct and lock the audit\n\n<Callout type=\"warning\">\n  Once you click **Complete**, the audit is finalised and cannot be edited. Make sure everything looks right before confirming.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nCatalog overview [#catalog-overview]\n\n| Tab         | What it's for                                              |\n| ----------- | ---------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Services    | The treatments your team performs                          |\n| Products    | Retail and consumable items, with automatic stock tracking |\n| Memberships | Prepaid session bundles for specific services              |\n| Vouchers    | Gift cards and discount codes                              |\n| Stock Audit | Count your physical stock and spot any discrepancies       |\n\n\n# Checkout (/docs/checkout)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCheckout is how you collect payment after a client's visit. The whole process happens in a panel that slides in from the right — no page navigation needed.\n\n<img alt=\"Checkout Process\" src=\"__img0\" />\n\n***\n\nStarting a checkout [#starting-a-checkout]\n\n<Steps>\n  <Step>\n    On the Calendar, click on the appointment card you want to check out.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    In the **Edit Appointment** panel that opens, click the **Checkout** button at the bottom right.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    The checkout screen slides in from the right, showing the client's name and the services from the appointment already loaded.\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\n***\n\nThe checkout screen [#the-checkout-screen]\n\nThe checkout screen is split into two areas:\n\n**Left — Payment**\r\nChoose how the client is paying. The available options are shown as cards:\n\n| Option            | Description                                            |\n| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |\n| **Card**          | Credit or debit card                                   |\n| **Cash**          | Pay with cash                                          |\n| **Membership**    | Redeem a pre-paid session from the client's membership |\n| **Online**        | Online payment                                         |\n| **Split Payment** | Divide the bill across more than one payment method    |\n\nClick the option that applies. The selected method will be highlighted.\n\n**Right — Order summary**\r\nShows the client's name and phone number, the services being charged, and a full summary:\n\n* Total amount (excluding discounts)\n* Subtotal (after any discount)\n* VAT (5%)\n* **Total due**\n* The chosen payment method and amount\n\n***\n\nApplying discounts, tips, and vouchers [#applying-discounts-tips-and-vouchers]\n\nAt the bottom left of the checkout screen, click the &#x2A;*···** (three dots) button to reveal additional options:\n\n| Option             | What it does                                     |\n| ------------------ | ------------------------------------------------ |\n| **Apply Discount** | Add a fixed or percentage discount to the sale   |\n| **Add Tip**        | Add a gratuity for the staff member              |\n| **Split Payment**  | Divide the total across multiple payment methods |\n| **Apply Voucher**  | Redeem a voucher code to reduce the balance      |\n\n***\n\nCompleting the payment [#completing-the-payment]\n\nOnce you've selected the payment method and applied any discounts or tips, click the &#x2A;*Pay AED \\[amount]** button at the bottom right to finalise the sale.\n\n***\n\nSale receipt [#sale-receipt]\n\nAfter payment is confirmed, the **Sale Receipt** screen appears. The header turns green and shows a **Paid** badge confirming the transaction is complete.\n\nFrom here you can:\n\nPrint the receipt [#print-the-receipt]\n\nClick the **print icon** (or the document icon for A4) to open the **Invoice Preview**. You'll see two format options:\n\n* **Thermal Receipt (80mm)** — formatted for a POS receipt printer\n* **Standard Invoice (A4)** — a full-page formatted tax invoice\n\nBoth formats show:\n\n* Your salon name, TRN, and branch location\n* Invoice number, date, time, and receptionist\n* Customer name and phone\n* Services performed and the staff team\n* Subtotal, VAT (5%), and total\n* How the sale was paid\n* \"Thank you for your visit!\" at the bottom\n\nFor **Thermal Receipt**, you can **Download PDF** or **Browser Print**.\r\nFor **Standard Invoice**, click **Print**.\n\nView the client's profile [#view-the-clients-profile]\n\nFrom the sale receipt screen you can navigate directly to the client's full profile to see their history, memberships, and vouchers.\n\nVoid a sale [#void-a-sale]\n\nIf a mistake was made, click the **Void Sale** button (shown in red on the right side of the receipt screen). This will cancel the transaction and reverse the sale record.\n\n<img alt=\"Voiding a Sale\" src=\"__img1\" />\n\n<Callout type=\"warning\">\n  Voiding a sale cannot be undone. Only void a sale if you're certain there was an error — for example, the wrong client was charged or the wrong services were added.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nCheckout summary [#checkout-summary]\n\n| Step                              | What happens                                      |\n| --------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- |\n| Click Checkout on the appointment | Checkout panel slides in with services pre-loaded |\n| Choose a payment method           | Card, Cash, Membership, Online, or Split          |\n| Apply extras via ··· menu         | Discount, tip, split payment, or voucher          |\n| Click Pay                         | Sale is recorded and receipt screen appears       |\n| Print receipt                     | Choose Thermal (80mm) or Standard Invoice (A4)    |\n| Void Sale                         | Cancels and reverses the transaction if needed    |\n\n\n# Clients (/docs/clients)\n\n\n\nThe Client List is your salon's client database. Every person who visits your salon can have a profile here, making it easy to look them up, track their history, and manage their memberships and vouchers.\n\nClick **Clients** in the left menu to get started.\n\n***\n\nThe client list [#the-client-list]\n\nThe main view shows a table of all your clients with the following columns:\n\n| Column        | What it shows                              |\n| ------------- | ------------------------------------------ |\n| Client name   | Name with an avatar (initials if no photo) |\n| Mobile number | Their phone number                         |\n| Reviews       | Internal reviews added by your team        |\n| Sales         | Total amount spent across all visits       |\n| Created at    | When the client was added to the system    |\n\nUse the **search bar** at the top to find anyone by name, email, or phone number.\n\nThe list is paginated — use the **Previous / Next** buttons at the bottom to navigate, and adjust the **Show** dropdown to control how many results appear per page.\n\n***\n\nAdding a new client [#adding-a-new-client]\n\n<Steps>\n  <Step>\n    Click the **+ Add** button in the top right corner. A form will pop up.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Fill in the client's details:\n\n    * **First Name** (required)\n    * **Last Name**\n    * **Phone Number** (required — select the country code from the dropdown)\n    * **Email**\n    * **Date of Birth**\n    * **Notes** — any internal notes about the client\n    * **Location** — assign them to a specific branch\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Click **Save Client**. They'll appear in the list and be available for booking straight away.\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\n<Callout type=\"tip\">\n  You can also add a client on the spot while booking an appointment in the Calendar — no need to come here first.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nViewing a client's profile [#viewing-a-clients-profile]\n\nClick on any client's name to open their full profile in a panel. The profile has three sections:\n\n**Left — Client details**\n\n* Name, phone, and email\n* **Edit client** — update any of their details\n* **Add review** — leave an internal note or review about this client\n* Date of birth (can be added here if not set)\n* Date the client was added to the system\n\n**Middle — Navigation tabs**\nSwitch between different parts of the client's history:\n\n| Tab          | What it shows                                                  |\n| ------------ | -------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Appointments | All appointments with status (Paid, Scheduled, No Show, etc.)  |\n| Sales        | All completed sales with service name, total, and View Details |\n| Products     | Products purchased by this client                              |\n| Vouchers     | Vouchers linked to this client                                 |\n| Memberships  | Active and completed membership packages with session counts   |\n| Loyalty      | Loyalty programme activity                                     |\n\n**Right — Detail view**\nClicking any item in the tabs shows the full detail. For example, clicking a sale opens the VAT invoice with the service, staff, subtotal, VAT, and total — with options to print or void the sale.\n\n***\n\nQuick reference [#quick-reference]\n\n| Feature         | Details                                                           |\n| --------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Search          | By name, email, or phone                                          |\n| Add client form | First name, phone required — email, DOB, notes, location optional |\n| Sales total     | Shown directly in the client list                                 |\n| Full profile    | Appointments, Sales, Products, Vouchers, Memberships, Loyalty     |\n| Quick add       | Create a client directly from the Calendar while booking          |\n\n\n# Commission (/docs/commission)\n\n\n\nThe Commission page is where you define how much each staff member earns from the services they perform, and view a live breakdown of what they've earned. NxCut calculates everything automatically based on real sales data.\n\nClick **Commission** in the left menu to get started.\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n  Commission is only accessible to admin users.\n</Callout>\n\nThe page is split into two sections: **Team Member Commissions** (your commission rules) and **Commission Calculations** (the live earnings breakdown).\n\n***\n\nTeam Member Commissions [#team-member-commissions]\n\nThis section lists all the commission rules you've set up. If no rules have been created yet, it will show \"No commission settings found — add a commission setting to get started.\"\n\n***\n\nSetting up a commission rule [#setting-up-a-commission-rule]\n\nClick **+ Add Commission** in the top right. A form will pop up.\n\n<Steps>\n  <Step>\n    Select a **Team Member** from the dropdown.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    The **Services Commission** section is enabled by default. This means the staff member earns commission on the services they perform.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Choose the **Default commission type**:\n\n    * **Fixed rate** — a set percentage applied to every sale they make\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Enter the **Default rate** — the percentage they'll earn (e.g., 30%).\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Set the **Sales period** — how often commission is calculated. The default is **Monthly**. NxCut will show you exactly when the first and following periods will be.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Use the **Sample calculation** box to double-check your setup. Enter a sale amount and NxCut will show you the exact commission calculation — including the threshold, commissionable amount, and final payout.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Click **Create Commission** to save.\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\n<Callout type=\"tip\">\n  The sample calculation updates in real time as you type — use it to make sure the numbers look right before saving.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nCommission Calculations [#commission-calculations]\n\nBelow the commission rules is the **Commission Calculations** table — a live breakdown of what each staff member has earned for the current period.\n\nAt the top you'll see four summary cards:\n\n| Card             | What it shows                             |\n| ---------------- | ----------------------------------------- |\n| Team Members     | Number of staff with sales in this period |\n| Total Sales      | Combined revenue across all staff         |\n| Total Commission | Total commission owed to the team         |\n| Avg Commission % | Average commission rate across the team   |\n\nThe table below shows each staff member with:\n\n* **Sales Count** — number of sales completed\n* **Total Sales** — their total revenue\n* **Commission Type** — their commission setup, or a **No Setup** badge if none has been configured\n* **Commission Rate** — their percentage\n* **Commission Amount** — what they've earned\n* **Actions** — an eye icon to view the breakdown, and a salary slip icon to open their slip\n\nClick **Export CSV** to download the full table for payroll processing.\n\n***\n\nSalary Slip [#salary-slip]\n\nClick the salary slip icon next to any team member to open their **Salary Slip**. This is a full payroll breakdown that can be filled in and downloaded.\n\nThe slip is headed with your salon's name and labelled as **Payroll Advice**. It shows the staff member's name, their occupancy percentage, free hours, the month, and their title.\n\n**Earnings section**\n\nA table where you can enter values for each earning type:\n\n| Earning      | Description                   |\n| ------------ | ----------------------------- |\n| Basic Salary | Their fixed monthly salary    |\n| Over Time    | Overtime hours worked         |\n| Voucher      | Commission from voucher sales |\n| Allowance    | Any allowances paid           |\n| Products     | Commission from product sales |\n| Bonus        | Any bonus payment             |\n| EOS          | End of service accrual        |\n| Target       | Target-based incentives       |\n\nEach row has editable fields for rate, days, and hours. The **Total Earning** is calculated automatically.\n\n**Deductions section**\n\nEnter any amounts to deduct:\n\n* Deduction\n* Cash advance\n* Additional deduction\n\nThe **Total Deduction** and final **Net Salary** are calculated automatically at the bottom.\n\nOnce the slip is complete, click **Download XLS** to save it as a spreadsheet, or **Close** to exit without saving.\n\n***\n\nQuick reference [#quick-reference]\n\n| Feature            | Details                                                                             |\n| ------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Commission rules   | Set per staff member with a fixed rate and sales period                             |\n| Sample calculator  | Preview the commission payout before saving                                         |\n| No Setup badge     | Staff member has sales but no commission rule configured                            |\n| Calculations table | Live monthly breakdown per staff member                                             |\n| Export CSV         | Download the full calculations for payroll                                          |\n| Salary slip        | Full payroll advice with earnings, deductions, and net salary — downloadable as XLS |\n| Access             | Admin only                                                                          |\n\n\n# Dashboard (/docs/dashboard)\n\n\n\n\n\nThe Dashboard is the first thing you see when you log in as an admin. It gives you a quick, up-to-date picture of how your salon is performing — without having to dig through reports or spreadsheets.\n\n<img alt=\"Dashboard Overview\" src=\"__img0\" />\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n  The Dashboard is only visible to admin users.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nFiltering by Date Range [#filtering-by-date-range]\n\nAt the top of the Dashboard is the **Filter by Date Range** bar. By default the dashboard shows recent data, but you can narrow it down to any period you want.\n\n<Steps>\n  <Step>\n    Click **Show Calendar** on the right side of the filter bar. A two-month calendar picker will appear.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Click a **start date**, then click an **end date**. The selected range will be highlighted between the two dates.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    The entire Dashboard updates automatically to reflect only that period.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Click **Hide Calendar** to close the picker when you're done.\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\n<Callout type=\"tip\">\n  Use the &#x2A;*\\<*&#x2A; and &#x2A;*>** arrows on the calendar to navigate to earlier or later months.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nSales by Location [#sales-by-location]\n\nA donut chart showing total revenue broken down by location. Below the chart you'll see the grand total and how many locations are currently active.\n\nThis gives you an instant feel for which branches are driving the most revenue — especially useful if you run multiple locations.\n\n***\n\nPayment Methods [#payment-methods]\n\nA donut chart right next to Sales by Location, showing how your revenue was collected — broken down by payment method (Cash, Card, Online, Membership, etc.).\n\nBelow the chart, each payment method is listed with its exact total for the period. Use this to see whether clients prefer paying by card or cash, or to verify totals against your till at the end of the day.\n\n***\n\nRecent Sales [#recent-sales]\n\n**All locations · Last 7 days**\n\nA summary card showing:\n\n* **Total revenue** collected over the last 7 days\n* **Number of appointments** completed\n* **Appointments value** — the combined price of all booked services\n\nBelow the numbers, a **line chart** tracks revenue and appointment count day by day so you can spot your busiest days and see whether bookings are translating into actual sales.\n\n***\n\nUpcoming Appointments [#upcoming-appointments]\n\n**All locations · Next 7 days**\n\nA summary card showing what's on the books:\n\n* Total appointments booked\n* How many are **confirmed**\n* How many have been **cancelled**\n\nA **bar chart** breaks this down day by day — great for spotting gaps in the schedule or flagging a day that has an unusually high cancellation rate.\n\n***\n\nAppointments Activity [#appointments-activity]\n\nA live feed of the most recent appointment events across all your locations — new bookings, updates, checkouts, and cancellations. Each entry shows the date, time, service, client (or Walk-In), duration, and which staff member is assigned.\n\nThis is your go-to for staying on top of last-minute changes, especially if you're managing more than one location.\n\n***\n\nToday's Next Appointments [#todays-next-appointments]\n\nA list of the remaining appointments for today, sorted by time. Each entry shows:\n\n* The appointment time\n* The service being performed\n* The client's name (or Walk-In)\n* The staff member handling it\n* The status badge (e.g., **Booked**)\n\nUse this for a quick check of what's still to come in the day.\n\n***\n\nTop Services [#top-services]\n\nA table showing which services are being booked the most, ranked by volume.\n\n| Column     | What it shows                           |\n| ---------- | --------------------------------------- |\n| Service    | The name of the treatment               |\n| This month | How many times it was booked this month |\n| Last month | Last month's count for comparison       |\n\n<Callout type=\"tip\">\n  Click on any service name to jump straight to that service in your Catalog.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nTop Team Members [#top-team-members]\n\nA table ranking your staff by total sales for the selected month. You can search by name and filter by month and year.\n\n| Column      | What it shows                               |\n| ----------- | ------------------------------------------- |\n| Team member | Staff member's name                         |\n| This month  | Total sales value for the current month     |\n| Last month  | Last month's total for comparison           |\n| Actions     | Generate a salary slip for that team member |\n\nThe **Actions** column has a salary slip icon — click it to open a formatted breakdown of that person's services, commission, and total payout for the period.\n\nYou can also export the full table using the **CSV**, **Excel**, or **PDF** buttons in the top-right corner.\n\n***\n\nCommission Calculations [#commission-calculations]\n\nAt the bottom of the Dashboard is the **Commission Calculations** widget. It shows a live summary of what each staff member has earned in commission for the selected month.\n\nAt the top of the widget you'll see four summary numbers:\n\n* **Team Members** — how many staff have sales this period\n* **Total Sales** — combined revenue across all staff\n* **Total Commission** — total commission owed\n* **Avg Commission %** — average commission rate across the team\n\nBelow that, the table shows each team member with:\n\n* Their number of sales\n* Their total sales value\n* Their commission type (or **No Setup** if commission hasn't been configured yet)\n* Their commission rate and calculated amount\n* An eye icon to view their breakdown and a salary slip icon to generate their slip\n\nFilter by month and year using the dropdowns at the top of the widget. The date range being shown is displayed at the bottom of the table.\n\n***\n\nDashboard Overview [#dashboard-overview]\n\n| Section                   | What it tells you                                    |\n| ------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |\n| Date range filter         | Narrow all dashboard data to any period              |\n| Sales by Location         | Revenue breakdown by branch                          |\n| Payment Methods           | How revenue was collected (cash, card, online, etc.) |\n| Recent Sales              | Last 7 days revenue with a daily trend chart         |\n| Upcoming Appointments     | Next 7 days bookings — confirmed vs. cancelled       |\n| Appointments Activity     | Live feed of the latest appointment events           |\n| Today's Next Appointments | What's still happening today                         |\n| Top Services              | Most booked services this month vs. last             |\n| Top Team Members          | Top earners with salary slip and export              |\n| Commission Calculations   | Monthly commission summary per staff member          |\n\n\n# Welcome to NxCut (/docs)\n\n\n\nWelcome to **NxCut** — your all-in-one salon management system. Whether you're booking an appointment, collecting payment, managing your team, or checking how your business is doing, everything you need is right here.\n\nThis guide walks you through every part of NxCut in plain, simple language. No technical experience needed.\n\n***\n\nWhat can NxCut do for you? [#what-can-nxcut-do-for-you]\n\n<Cards>\n  <Card title=\"Dashboard\" href=\"/docs/dashboard\" description=\"See how your business is doing at a glance — revenue, appointments, and top performers.\" />\n\n  <Card title=\"Calendar & Bookings\" href=\"/docs/calendar\" description=\"Book, reschedule, and manage appointments for your whole team in one view.\" />\n\n  <Card title=\"Checkout\" href=\"/docs/checkout\" description=\"Collect payment, apply discounts, add tips, and split bills — all in a few clicks.\" />\n\n  <Card title=\"Sales Hub\" href=\"/docs/sales\" description=\"View your full sales history — payments, memberships, vouchers, tips, and more.\" />\n\n  <Card title=\"Catalog & Inventory\" href=\"/docs/catalog\" description=\"Set up your services, products, membership packages, and gift vouchers.\" />\n\n  <Card title=\"Clients\" href=\"/docs/clients\" description=\"Keep a full record of every client — their visits, memberships, and voucher balances.\" />\n\n  <Card title=\"Team Management\" href=\"/docs/team\" description=\"Add staff, set their working hours, and control what they can access.\" />\n\n  <Card title=\"Commission\" href=\"/docs/commission\" description=\"Automatically calculate how much each team member earns and generate salary slips.\" />\n\n  <Card title=\"Reporting\" href=\"/docs/reporting\" description=\"Dig into your numbers — sales trends, payment breakdowns, tips, and more.\" />\n\n  <Card title=\"Settings\" href=\"/docs/settings\" description=\"Set up your locations, business hours, payment options, and access rules.\" />\n\n  <Card title=\"Website & Booking Page\" href=\"/docs/website\" description=\"Manage your public booking page and let clients book appointments online.\" />\n</Cards>\n\n***\n\nFinding your way around [#finding-your-way-around]\n\nWhen you log in, you'll see a menu on the left side of the screen. Each item takes you to a different part of NxCut.\n\n| Section                        | What it's for                     | Who can see it |\n| ------------------------------ | --------------------------------- | -------------- |\n| [Dashboard](/docs/dashboard)   | Business overview and key numbers | Admins only    |\n| [Calendar](/docs/calendar)     | Appointments and bookings         | All staff      |\n| [Sales](/docs/sales)           | Sales history and transactions    | All staff      |\n| [Clients](/docs/clients)       | Client directory and profiles     | All staff      |\n| [Catalog](/docs/catalog)       | Services, products, and packages  | All staff      |\n| [Team](/docs/team)             | Staff profiles and schedules      | All staff      |\n| [Commission](/docs/commission) | Earnings and salary slips         | Admins only    |\n| [Reports](/docs/reporting)     | Financial reports and analytics   | Admins only    |\n| [Settings](/docs/settings)     | Business configuration            | Admins only    |\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n  **Admin vs. Staff** — Admin users can access everything. Regular staff only see what they need for their daily work: Calendar, Sales, Clients, Catalog, and Team.\n</Callout>\n\n\n# Reporting & Analytics (/docs/reporting)\n\n\n\nThe Reports section gives you a deeper look at your salon's performance beyond the day-to-day. All reports are filterable, exportable, and organised by category so you can find what you need quickly.\n\nClick **Reports** in the left menu to get started.\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n  Reports are only accessible to admin users.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nFinding a report [#finding-a-report]\n\nThe main reports page shows all available reports as cards. You can:\n\n* **Search** by report name or description\n* **Filter by creator** using the All creators dropdown\n* **Filter by type** using the All reports dropdown\n* **Browse by category** using the tabs across the top: All reports · Sales · Finance · Appointments · Team · Clients · Inventory\n\nThe left sidebar organises reports into:\n\n| Category    | What's in it                                         |\n| ----------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |\n| All reports | Every report in one place                            |\n| Favourites  | Reports you've starred for quick access              |\n| Dashboards  | Visual overview reports (e.g. Performance dashboard) |\n| Premium     | Premium-tier reports                                 |\n| Folders     | Custom folders you create to organise reports        |\n\nStar any report card to add it to your **Favourites**.\n\n***\n\nAvailable reports [#available-reports]\n\nPerformance Dashboard [#performance-dashboard]\n\n*(Dashboards)*\n\nA visual overview of your salon's performance. Shows key metrics, charts, and trends across revenue, appointments, services, and staff — all in one place.\n\n***\n\nSales Log [#sales-log]\n\n*(Sales)*\n\nA detailed record of every sale — including the services sold, discounts applied, payment methods used, staff member, and client. Use this when you need to trace a specific transaction or review sales over a period.\n\n**Filters:** Date range, location, team member, client, payment method.\n\n**Export:** CSV, Excel, PDF.\n\n***\n\nFinance Summary [#finance-summary]\n\n*(Finance)*\n\nA period-by-period breakdown of your sales, payments, and liabilities. Perfect for month-end reviews and accounting.\n\nChoose how to group the data:\n\n| Period  | What you'll see                  |\n| ------- | -------------------------------- |\n| Day     | Last 30 days, one column per day |\n| Week    | Last 4 weeks                     |\n| Month   | Last 6 months (default)          |\n| Quarter | Last 4 quarters                  |\n| Year    | Last 3 years                     |\n\n**Export:** CSV, Excel, PDF.\n\n***\n\nPayment Transactions [#payment-transactions]\n\n*(Finance)*\n\nA full log of every individual payment collected. Use this to verify payment method totals or trace a specific transaction.\n\n**Filters:** Date range, location, team member, payment method, transaction type, amount range.\n\n**Export:** CSV, Excel, PDF.\n\n***\n\nTips Summary [#tips-summary]\n\n*(Team)*\n\nAn overview of all tips received, broken down by staff member. Shows total tips, number of tipped transactions, average tip, and tip percentage for each person.\n\n**Filters:** Date range, location, team member, payment method.\n\n**Export:** CSV, Excel, PDF.\n\n***\n\nExport options [#export-options]\n\nAll reports can be exported in:\n\n| Format        | Best for                                |\n| ------------- | --------------------------------------- |\n| CSV           | Importing into a spreadsheet            |\n| Excel (.xlsx) | A formatted, ready-to-share spreadsheet |\n| PDF           | Printing or sharing outside the system  |\n\n***\n\nDate range options [#date-range-options]\n\nAll reports use the same date picker with quick presets:\n\n* Today / Yesterday\n* Last 7, 30, or 90 days\n* Last week / Last month / Last 3, 6, or 12 months\n* Week-to-date / Month-to-date / Quarter-to-date / Year-to-date\n* Custom start and end date\n\n\n# Sales Hub (/docs/sales)\n\n\n\nThe Sales Hub is your complete record of everything that's been sold or paid for. Click **Sales** in the left menu and you'll see a sidebar with eight sections. Each one is focused on a different part of your business and has its own search, date filter, and **Export** button.\n\n***\n\nDaily Sales [#daily-sales]\n\n**Sales → Daily Sales**\n\nYour end-of-day summary. Use the **Today*&#x2A;, &#x2A;*\\<*&#x2A;, and &#x2A;*>** buttons to pick any day and see a full breakdown of what happened.\n\nThe page is split into three parts:\n\n**Transaction summary**\nA table showing what was sold by item type (e.g., Service, Product), how many were sold, and the net total.\n\n**Cash movement summary**\nA breakdown of how payments were collected — showing each payment method (Cash, Online, Card, etc.) and the amount collected through each. Also shows the total **Payments collected** and how much of that was **tips**.\n\n**Summary bar**\nFour quick-view numbers at the bottom:\n\n* **Total Sales** — total revenue for the day\n* **Total Transactions** — number of completed transactions\n* **Sale Types** — how many different item types were sold\n* **Payment Methods** — how many different payment methods were used\n\n***\n\nAppointments [#appointments]\n\n**Sales → Appointments**\n\nA full list of every appointment-based sale. Use this when you need to look up a specific service, client visit, or check what was charged and whether a discount was applied.\n\n**Columns:** Sale ID · Client (name + phone) · Service · Sale Date · Team Member · Unit Price · Quantity · Discount · Total Price\n\nDiscounts show in red when applied. Search by client name or service, or filter by date range. Click **Export** to download as CSV.\n\n***\n\nSales Transactions [#sales-transactions]\n\n**Sales → Sales**\n\nYour complete transaction history across all sale types. By default it shows the last 30 days.\n\n**Columns:** Sale ID · Payment Date · Client · Team Members · Payment Method · Tips · Status · Amount\n\nThe **Status** column shows either:\n\n* **Completed** — the sale went through successfully\n* **Voided** (red badge) — the sale was reversed after the fact\n\nClick any **Sale ID** to open the full [Sale Details panel](#sale-details).\n\nClick any **Client name** to open their [Client Profile](#client-profile).\n\n***\n\nPayments [#payments]\n\n**Sales → Payments**\n\nEvery payment transaction that was successfully collected — similar to Sales Transactions but focused on the payment side only. Voided sales are excluded here.\n\n**Columns:** Sale ID · Payment Date · Client · Team Members · Payment Method · Tips · Status · Amount\n\nTips show in the Tips column when they were added to the sale. Search by client name or sale ID, or filter by date range.\n\n***\n\nMemberships [#memberships]\n\n**Sales → Memberships**\n\nAll membership packages that have been sold, with live session tracking.\n\n**Columns:** Purchase Date · Client · Membership name · Service · Sessions (used / remaining with a progress bar) · Cost · Status\n\nThe **Status** shows either **Active** (sessions still available) or **Completed** (all sessions used). The progress bar makes it easy to see at a glance how far through a package a client is.\n\n***\n\nVouchers [#vouchers]\n\n**Sales → Vouchers**\n\nAll vouchers that have been purchased or redeemed. Search by client name, voucher name, or voucher code. Filter by date range to narrow results.\n\n***\n\nProducts [#products]\n\n**Sales → Products**\n\nA record of every product sold, with live stock levels.\n\n**Columns:** Sale ID · Product Name · Category · Brand · Quantity · Unit Price · Total Price · Current Stock · Sale Date · Status\n\nThe **Current Stock** column shows a warning icon (⚠) when stock is running low. The **Status** badge will show **Low Stock** to flag items that need reordering.\n\nSearch by product name, SKU, barcode, or category.\n\n***\n\nTips [#tips]\n\n**Sales → Tips**\n\nEvery tip that's been collected, attributed to the staff member who received it.\n\n**Columns:** Sale ID · Tip Amount · Staff Member · Payment Method · Sale Total · Date\n\nSearch by staff name, payment method, or sale ID. Filter by date range.\n\n***\n\nClient Profile [#client-profile]\n\nAnywhere you see a **client name** shown as a blue link (in Sales Transactions, Payments, etc.), you can click it to open that client's full profile in a panel on the right.\n\nThe profile is split into two parts:\n\n**Left — Client details**\n\n* Name, phone, and email\n* **Edit client** — update their contact details\n* **Add review** — add an internal note or review about the client\n* Date of birth (optional)\n* Date the client was created in the system\n\n**Middle — Navigation tabs**\nSwitch between different views of the client's history:\n\n| Tab          | What it shows                                                      |\n| ------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n| Appointments | All appointments with status badges (Paid, Scheduled, No Show)     |\n| Sales        | All completed sales with service, total, and a View Details button |\n| Products     | Products purchased by this client                                  |\n| Vouchers     | Vouchers associated with this client                               |\n| Memberships  | Active and completed membership packages (shows count badge)       |\n| Loyalty      | Loyalty programme activity                                         |\n\n**Right — Detail view**\nClicking any item in the tabs shows the full detail on the right side. For example, clicking a sale shows the service, time, staff, subtotal, VAT, and total.\n\n***\n\nSale Details [#sale-details]\n\nClicking a **Sale ID** or **View Details** anywhere in the Sales Hub opens the full Sale Details panel. This shows:\n\n* **Status badge** (e.g., Completed)\n* Client name and phone\n* **VAT Invoice** number and date\n* Services performed with time, duration, and assigned team\n* **Staff Information** — assigned staff member and receptionist\n* Subtotal, VAT (5%), and Total\n* **Print icons** — print as thermal receipt or standard A4 invoice\n* **Sale-ID** (copyable)\n* **Void Sale** button — reverses the transaction if an error was made\n* **Back to Appointment** button — returns to the linked appointment\n\n<Callout type=\"warning\">\n  Voiding a sale cannot be undone. Only use this if there was a genuine error with the transaction.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nQuick reference [#quick-reference]\n\n| Section            | Best used for                                           |\n| ------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Daily Sales        | End-of-day reconciliation — cash, card, and tips totals |\n| Appointments       | Looking up a specific service or client visit           |\n| Sales Transactions | Full transaction log including voided sales             |\n| Payments           | Collected payments only, with tips                      |\n| Memberships        | Session usage and package status                        |\n| Vouchers           | Gift card purchases and redemptions                     |\n| Products           | Retail sales with live stock levels                     |\n| Tips               | Gratuity records by staff member                        |\n\n\n# Settings (/docs/settings)\n\n\n\nSettings is where you control the core configuration of your salon. Click **Settings** in the left menu to get started. There are four sections: **Branches**, **Calendar**, **Payment Methods**, and **Permissions**.\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n  Settings is only accessible to admin users.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nBranches [#branches]\n\n**Settings → Branches**\n\nThe Branches page shows all your salon locations. Each branch is displayed as a card showing:\n\n* Branch photo\n* Branch name and **Active** status badge\n* Location ID\n* Number of staff assigned\n* Contact email and phone\n* City and country\n* TRN (Tax Registration Number)\n* Date the branch was created\n* A **pencil icon** to edit the branch\n\nEditing a branch [#editing-a-branch]\n\nClick the **pencil icon** on any branch card to open the Edit Branch form.\n\nFields you can update:\n\n* **Branch Name** (required)\n* **Email**\n* **Country** (with flag selector)\n* **City**\n* **Phone** (with country code selector)\n* **TRN** — your Tax Registration Number, printed on invoices\n* **Branch Images** — upload up to 4 photos to showcase the branch (shown on the card)\n\nClick **Update Branch** to save.\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n  The **Location ID** is shown at the top of the form but cannot be edited — it's a system-generated identifier.\n</Callout>\n\n<Callout type=\"warning\">\n  To add a new branch, contact NxCut support. Branch creation is managed at the account level and cannot be done directly from this page.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nCalendar [#calendar]\n\n**Settings → Calendar**\n\nThis is where you set your salon's **Global Working Hours** — the default opening and closing times that appear on the Calendar for all staff.\n\nThe hours are configured per location. You'll see \"Configuring for: \\[location name]\" at the top so you always know which branch you're editing.\n\nSetting your hours [#setting-your-hours]\n\nFor each day of the week (Sunday through Saturday), you can:\n\n* Set a **Start Time** and **End Time**\n* Tick the **Closed** checkbox if the salon is closed that day — it will be hidden from the Calendar entirely\n* Click **Default** on any day to reset it to the default hours\n\nDefault hours are **08:00 AM – 11:45 PM**.\n\nOnce you've made your changes, click **Save Global Hours**. To reset all days back to the defaults at once, click **Reset to Default**.\n\n<Callout type=\"warning\">\n  The end time must always be later than the start time. Invalid entries will not be saved.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nPayment Methods [#payment-methods]\n\n**Settings → Payment Methods**\n\nThis page shows all the payment options available at checkout. The default methods are: **Card**, **Cash**, **Membership**, **Online**, **Split Payment**, and **Voucher** — all active by default.\n\nEach method is shown as a card with its name, **Active** status badge, and the date it was created.\n\nAdding a payment method [#adding-a-payment-method]\n\nClick **+ Add Payment Method**, enter a name, and save. The new method will immediately be available at checkout.\n\nEditing or deleting a payment method [#editing-or-deleting-a-payment-method]\n\nClick the &#x2A;*···** (three dots) on any card to reveal two options:\n\n* **Edit** — rename the method or change its status\n* **Delete** (red) — permanently remove it\n\n<Callout type=\"warning\">\n  Deleting a payment method is permanent. If you just want to stop it appearing at checkout temporarily, edit it and set it to inactive instead.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nPermissions [#permissions]\n\n**Settings → Permissions**\n\nPermissions let you control the rules around tips and discounts at checkout. Settings are per location — select the location you want to configure from the **Location** dropdown at the top.\n\nThere are three permission settings:\n\nAllow Voucher Usage for Tips [#allow-voucher-usage-for-tips]\n\n**Toggle: Enable Voucher Tips**\n\nWhen turned on, clients can use a voucher as the payment method when adding a tip at checkout.\n\n*Off by default.*\n\n***\n\nAccept Tips Online Only [#accept-tips-online-only]\n\n**Toggle: Disable Tips in POS**\n\nWhen turned on, the ability to add tips is completely removed from the POS checkout screen. Tips would only be accepted through online bookings.\n\n*Off by default.*\n\n***\n\nPrevent Tips with Manual Discount [#prevent-tips-with-manual-discount]\n\n**Toggle: Enforce Mutual Exclusivity**\n\nWhen turned on, a staff member cannot apply both a manual discount and a tip to the same sale. If a discount is applied, the tip option is disabled — and vice versa.\n\n*Off by default.*\n\n\n# Team Management (/docs/team)\n\n\n\nThe Team Management page is where you manage everyone who works at your salon — their profiles, working hours, service permissions, and login accounts.\n\nClick **Team** in the left menu to get started. The page is divided into two sections: **Team Members** and **Authenticated Users**.\n\n***\n\nTeam Members [#team-members]\n\nTeam Members are the staff profiles that appear on the Calendar. Each card shows the staff member's photo (or initials if no photo is set), their email, and phone number.\n\nEach card has three action buttons:\n\n* **Edit Shift** — set their weekly working hours\n* **Edit** — update their profile details\n* **Delete** (red trash icon) — remove them permanently\n\nTo view archived staff, toggle **Show archived team members only** in the top right corner.\n\n***\n\nAdding a team member [#adding-a-team-member]\n\nClick **+ Add → Add Team Member**. A form will pop up.\n\n<Steps>\n  <Step>\n    Click the &#x2A;*+** circle at the top to upload a profile photo (JPEG or PNG, under 2 MB). This is optional but recommended — it helps identify staff on the Calendar.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Enter their **First Name** (required) and **Last Name**.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Set a **Calendar Color** — this is the color used for their column on the Calendar. Each staff member should have a distinct color to make them easy to tell apart.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Optionally enter a **Team Member ID** — useful if your business uses internal staff ID numbers.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Set **Category Permissions** — toggle on the service categories this staff member is allowed to perform (e.g., Hair, Nails, Facial). All categories are enabled by default. Staff will only appear as a booking option for the categories you enable.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Toggle **Visible to Clients** on if this staff member should appear in client-facing booking. This is on by default.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Toggle **Admin User** on if they need full access to the system (Reports, Settings, Commission, Dashboard). Off by default.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Select a **Location** (required).\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Click **Add Team Member**.\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\n***\n\nEditing a team member [#editing-a-team-member]\n\nClick **Edit** on any team member card to update their photo, name, calendar color, category permissions, admin status, or location.\n\n<Callout type=\"warning\">\n  You cannot remove admin access from the last remaining admin. Make sure at least one other admin exists before making that change.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nSetting working hours (Edit Shift) [#setting-working-hours-edit-shift]\n\nEach staff member can have their own weekly schedule so the Calendar only shows them as available when they're actually working.\n\n<Steps>\n  <Step>\n    Click **Edit Shift** on the team member's card.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    For each day of the week, set their **start** and **finish time**.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Mark any day as **Off** if they don't work that day.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Click **Save**.\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\n***\n\nAuthenticated Users [#authenticated-users]\n\nThe **Authenticated Users** section sits below the team member grid and shows all staff login accounts. These cards have an **orange border** to distinguish them from team member profiles.\n\nEach card shows the user's name, their **Auth User** label, email address, and Location ID.\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n  A team member profile and a login account are two separate things. A team member profile controls how someone appears on the Calendar. A login account controls how they log in to NxCut. Most staff will need both.\n</Callout>\n\n***\n\nAdding a login account (Auth User) [#adding-a-login-account-auth-user]\n\nClick **+ Add → Add Auth User**. A form will pop up.\n\n<Steps>\n  <Step>\n    Enter their **Email** (required) — this will be their username when logging in.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Set a **Password** (required).\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Optionally enter a **Display Name** and **Phone Number**.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Toggle **Admin User** on if they should have full system access.\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Select a **Location** (required).\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step>\n    Click **Create User**. The account is active immediately.\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\n***\n\nArchiving a team member [#archiving-a-team-member]\n\nIf someone leaves but you want to keep their history in the system, archive them instead of deleting.\n\n* Open their profile and choose **Archive**.\n* Archived members are hidden from the default view.\n* Toggle **Show archived team members only** at the top of the page to find them again.\n\n***\n\nQuick reference [#quick-reference]\n\n| Feature              | Details                                                               |\n| -------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Profile photo        | JPEG or PNG, max 2 MB                                                 |\n| Calendar color       | Makes each staff member's column easy to identify                     |\n| Team Member ID       | Optional internal staff ID number                                     |\n| Category permissions | Per-category toggles — controls which services they can be booked for |\n| Working hours        | Set per staff member, per day of the week                             |\n| Auth users           | Separate login accounts shown with an orange border                   |\n| Admin access         | Grants full access to Reports, Settings, Commission, and Dashboard    |\n| Visible to clients   | Controls whether they appear in client-facing booking                 |\n\n\n# Components (/docs/test)\n\n\n\nCode Block [#code-block]\n\n```js\nconsole.log('Hello World');\n```\n\nCards [#cards]\n\n<Cards>\n  <Card title=\"Learn more about Next.js\" href=\"https://nextjs.org/docs\" />\n\n  <Card title=\"Learn more about Fumadocs\" href=\"https://fumadocs.dev\" />\n</Cards>\n\n\n# Website & Booking Module (/docs/website)\n\n\n\nNxCut automatically creates a public booking Module for your salon. Clients can visit it to browse your services, pick a staff member, choose a time, and book an appointment — without you needing to do anything to set it up.\n\nClick the **globe icon** in the left menu to manage your website settings.\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n  The Website section is only accessible to admin users.\n</Callout>\n\nAt the top right of the page you'll find two quick-access buttons:\n\n* **Booking Page** — opens your live client booking page in a new tab\n* **My Website** — opens your full salon website\n\n***\n\nEdit your profile [#edit-your-profile]\n\nThe first section lets you update your salon's basic public information.\n\n| Field         | What it's for                               |\n| ------------- | ------------------------------------------- |\n| Salon Name    | The name displayed on your booking page     |\n| Mobile Number | Your salon's contact number                 |\n| Email Address | Your contact email                          |\n| Owner Name    | The name of the salon owner                 |\n| Website       | Your auto-generated booking URL (read-only) |\n\nClick **Save Changes** when done.\n\n***\n\nWebsite Details [#website-details]\n\nCustomise how your booking page looks to clients.\n\n| Field              | What it's for                                                                   |\n| ------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Logo Text          | The text displayed as your logo                                                 |\n| Website Title      | The page title shown in the browser tab                                         |\n| Landing Page Image | The hero image at the top of your booking page (PNG, JPG, GIF or WebP, max 5MB) |\n\nClick **Upload Image** to add or replace the landing page photo, then click **Save Changes**.\n\n***\n\nContact Us [#contact-us]\n\nThis section shows the contact details displayed to clients on your booking page — your email address and WhatsApp number. These are pulled from your profile automatically.\n\n***\n\nHow the client booking flow works [#how-the-client-booking-flow-works]\n\nWhen a client visits your booking page, they go through a simple step-by-step process:\n\nStep 1 — Select a location [#step-1--select-a-location]\n\nThe client picks which branch they want to visit. If you only have one location, this step is skipped automatically.\n\nStep 2 — Browse the price menu [#step-2--browse-the-price-menu]\n\nServices are grouped by category (Facial, Hair, Nails, etc.). Prices include 5% VAT. The client taps a category to see the individual services and their prices, then selects the one they want.\n\nStep 3 — Pick a professional [#step-3--pick-a-professional]\n\nThe client chooses which staff member they'd like. They can pick a specific person or select **Any Agent** to be assigned to whoever is available.\n\nStep 4 — Choose a date and time [#step-4--choose-a-date-and-time]\n\nA calendar shows the current month. Days with available slots are marked with a **green underline**. The client clicks a date to see the available time slots for that day, then taps a green slot to reserve it.\n\nA **Summary*&#x2A; panel on the right shows the selected service, agent, and total price. The client can also click **+ Add More** to add additional services to the same booking.\n\nStep 5 — Enter contact details [#step-5--enter-contact-details]\n\nThe client fills in their information:\n\n* **New Client** — enters their details for the first time\n* **Existing Client** — enters their registered phone number to pull up their profile\n\nThey can also add any **special requests or notes** in the Additional Comments field.\n\nStep 6 — Appointment confirmed [#step-6--appointment-confirmed]\n\nAfter submitting, a confirmation screen appears showing:\n\n* A green **Appointment Confirmed** message\n* A unique &#x2A;*ORDER #** for reference\n* The date, time, service, agent, and location\n* **Add to Calendar** and **Print** buttons\n* A full **Cost Breakdown** showing the service price, any credits applied, and the balance due\n\nThe appointment is instantly added to your Calendar in NxCut and visible to the assigned staff member.\n"}